{
 "name": "RPlog_Senatorial_Inquiry",
 "title": "Senatorial Inquiry",
 "summary": "In a battered briefing room amid an active warzone on Mon Calamari, the Quarren senator Lavrish'lin confronts Marine captain Vengan Draelis and Sergeant Dagon over their unit's conduct during the bacta-refinery operation. The senator warns that taking a brain-tissue sample from a dead Quarren without sanction could expose the whole unit to war-crimes charges and hand the Empire propaganda to divide the Republic, insisting the Chief of State wants the unvarnished truth to mount a defense. Draelis refuses to be cowed, defending his battlefield decisions and accusing the senate of grandstanding, while the hot-headed Dagon needles the senator until tempers flare over the Marines' lethal tactics and the senator's jab at the Chief of State's age. The standoff turns to dueling recordings and accusations of falsified reports, and the inquiry ends acrimoniously with the Marines walking out as the building shakes from a nearby explosion.",
